
TASK:

Get the current networking configuration for your desktop.

Are you on a wired or a wireless connection? Or both?

If you have wireless hardware, see what wireless networks are available, if any.

SOLUTION:

Click the Network Manager icon in the upper right corner of your desktop (appearance can vary by distribution). This should bring up the wired and wireless connection state, and which wireless networks are available.

$ nmcli radio wifi on

$ nmcli radio wifi off
